This is the AmigaGuide® file Preview.guide, produced by Makeinfo-1.55 from 
the input file sD/Preview.texi.


@Node Main "Preview.guide"

@{b}MPMorph Preview@{ub} 4.4 Contents
****************************

@Remark $VER: MPMorph_Preview_guide 4.4 (23.2.97)

This ARexx script to MPMorph lets you preview a Morph.  Either a single
image or (with mkanim) an animation.

The following gadgets are displayed:


 @{" Mode         " Link "mode"}       Image or animation
 @{" Frame        " Link "frame"}       Frame to preview
 @{" frames       " Link "frames"}       Frames for animation
 @{" X Resolution " Link "X"}       Width of preview
 @{" Y Resolution " Link "Y"}       Height of preview
 @{" DX           " Link "DX"}       X to skip
 @{" DY           " Link "DY"}       Y to skip

There are also @{b}Ok@{ub} (shortcut @{b}O@{ub}), Help and @{b}Cancel@{ub} (shortcut @{b}C@{ub}) gadgets.


 @{" Index " Link "Index"}      Index to this guide


@EndNode

@Node "mode" "Preview.guide/mode"
@Next "frame"
@Prev "Main"
@Toc "Main"

Mode Gadget
***********

This selects either @{b}Single Image@{ub} or @{b}Animation@{ub}.

Mkanim is required to preview animations.

@{b}M@{ub} and @{b}m@{ub} can be used to cycle this gadget.


@EndNode

@Node "frame" "Preview.guide/frame"
@Next "frames"
@Prev "mode"
@Toc "Main"

Frame Gadget
************

This selects the frame to render for a single image. The default is the
frame half way through the morph.

This gadget is not available when previewing an animation.

@{b}F@{ub} and @{b}f@{ub} can be used to change the value of this gadget.


@EndNode

@Node "frames" "Preview.guide/frames"
@Next "X"
@Prev "frame"
@Toc "Main"

Frames Gadget
*************

This selects the number of frames to preview with an animation. The
default is 5.

This gadget is not available when previewing a single image.

@{b}R@{ub} and @{b}r@{ub} can be used to change the value of this gadget.


@EndNode

@Node "X" "Preview.guide/X"
@Next "Y"
@Prev "frames"
@Toc "Main"

X Resolution Gadget
*******************

This selects the width of the image to preview. The default is 128.

@{b}S@{ub} and @{b}s@{ub} can be used to change the value of this gadget.


@EndNode

@Node "Y" "Preview.guide/Y"
@Next "DX"
@Prev "X"
@Toc "Main"

Y Resolution Gadget
*******************

This selects the height of the image to preview. The default is 128.

@{b}L@{ub} and @{b}l@{ub} can be used to change the value of this gadget.


@EndNode

@Node "DX" "Preview.guide/DX"
@Next "DY"
@Prev "Y"
@Toc "Main"

DX Gadget
*********

This selects the X to skip. The default is 0. If set to e.g. 1 then
every other horizontal pixel will be rendered.

@{b}X@{ub} and @{b}x@{ub} can be used to change the value of this gadget.


@EndNode

@Node "DY" "Preview.guide/DY"
@Next "Index"
@Prev "DX"
@Toc "Main"

DY Gadget
*********

This selects the Y to skip. The default is 0. If set to e.g. 1 then
every other vertical pixel will be rendered.

@{b}Y@{ub} and @{b}y@{ub} can be used to change the value of this gadget.


@EndNode

@Node "Index" "Preview.guide/Index"
@Prev "DY"
@Toc "Main"

